Administrative Staff College of India (ASCI) and Namibia Institute of Public Administration and Management (NIPAM) have decided to establish technical cooperation in the areas of capacity building of public officials. As per the MoU, ASCI would customise capacity building programs for NIPAM in the area of public governance, public service delivery, administration and leadership for public officials of the Republic of Namibia besides taking up research in the field of governance.The MoU was signed in the presence of Chairman ASCI, K. Padmanabhaiah and Namibiaâ€™s Cabinet Secretary and de-facto Chairperson of the NIPAM governing council, George Simataa here on Thursday.